channel.title: Could someone teamviewer with me and help me fix my client error?
channel.description: please i need someone to help me fix my client error i been asking for a while now but no one knows what i talking about.. i need to fix this because when i change my ip it goes kinda like null for my offline client also.

item.title: Could someone teamviewer with me and help me fix my client error?
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“jmood128, post:17, topic:392624”][quote author=joelx617 link=topic=489797.msg3580978#msg3580978 date=1303785789]
wait so i dont type in like the ip such as 124.142.1.1 but i type in ip like kingspk.no-ip.info? into the client.java file?
[/quote]

Yes you put kingspk.no-ip.info into your client.java of your client, or what ever file is used to hold the address.[/quote]

Unless the server is running on the local machine. In that case you MUST use 127.0.0.1.

item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

You need to get the ip your router is giving your computer, I suggest you go to portforward.com. Also to get the ip of your computer just go to your start menu and hit run or if you’re using vista or windows 7 just type in cmd.exe and hit it, then type in ipconfig, and use the ipv4 address for the one you port forward with.

item.title: Could someone teamviewer with me and help me fix my client error?
item.dc:creator: @doom_j doom_j
item.description:
@doom_j wrote:

joelx617:

i change the original ip thats there which is something like 127.0.0…0 or something like that and i change to my router’s ip which i am port fowarding from. ? whats problem ?

I think that is the problem, your router isn’t hosting your server. Use the ip you created with no-ip. If that doesn’t work then either your computers fire wall is blocking it or your router is blocking it.
